{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/505", "repo": "rails", "body": "@fxn \r\n\r\n> As of today there's no builtin way to do partial updates, because there's no builtin way in HTTP\r\n\r\nit's already built into rails and works ok over HTTP, afaict:\r\n\r\n`curl -H \"Accept: application/json\" http://test.dev/widgets/1`\r\n\r\n`{\"id\":1,\"foo\":\"bar\", \"fizz\": \"buzz\", \"car\": \"blue\" }`\r\n\r\n`curl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X PUT -d \"{ \\\"foo\\\": \\\"partially updated\\\" }\" http://test.dev/widgets/1`\r\n\r\n`curl -H \"Accept: application/json\" http://test.dev/widgets/1`\r\n\r\n`{\"id\":1,\"foo\":\"partially updated\", \"fizz\": \"buzz\", \"car\": \"blue\" }`\r\n\r\n", "_id": {"$oid": "52385f14bd3543c151012148"}, "issue_id": 505, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3190662", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/505#issuecomment-3190662", "updated_at": "2011-12-17T18:20:07Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly", "login": "mikekelly", "gravatar_id": "fddf4e0508e0ab09171063fc13062b85", "html_url": "https://github.com/mikekelly", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/fddf4e0508e0ab09171063fc13062b85?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F425fbd8cd12d7ed14264bdd50d8da0b1.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 55782, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/followers", "type": "Us